Fix: missing left border on active right-hand segmented toggle button

The `.view-toggle` segmented control strips the left border between its
two buttons (`border-left: none`) to avoid a doubled-up divider. This is
correct for the inactive state, but when the *second* (right) button
becomes `.active`, it inherited the accent-colored border on three sides
only -- the left edge was left as `none`, so the outline looked broken/
open on that side.

Fix: restore a 1px accent-colored left border specifically when the
second button in the group is active.

--- a/src/styles.css
+++ b/src/styles.css
@@ -216,7 +216,8 @@
 /* ---- ship browser: view toggle + list view ---- */
 .view-toggle { display: flex; gap: 0; margin-left: auto; }
 .view-toggle button { border-radius: 4px 0 0 4px; }
 .view-toggle button + button { border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0; border-left: none; }
 .view-toggle .active { border-color: var(--accent); color: var(--accent); position: relative; z-index: 1; }
+.view-toggle button + button.active { border-left: 1px solid var(--accent); }
 .result-count { color: var(--dim); font-size: 12px; margin-bottom: 8px; font-family: var(--mono); }
